summary:
Besides my interest in rollercoasters, football, billiards and board games, I am driven by my intellectual curiosity in developing strategies to solve problems. 

With my refined skills set I bring tailor-made solutions that enables organisations to innovate, Implement and thrive globally.

Throughout my career, either working alone or in a team, I’ve consistently met and exceeded my quota as a Management Consultant. 

I have extensive knowledge in the major forces which contributes to the overall growth of a business.

[{'date': {'start': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}, 'end': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': None}}, 'role': 'Founder', 'company': {'id': None, 'name': 'Development for African Female', 'logo': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4D0BAQH2L2sJzsyVYQ/company-logo_400_400/0/1519881813501?e=1700697600&v=beta&t=1E2iPUx13h7vETr0XZLpZrE97jx3iHDU_BuD-atV2rw', 'url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/development-for-african-female/'}, 'cause': 'EDUCATION', 'description': 'About 
Development for African female is a charity registry  No. 319/G.37/D14/VOL II /SAAJP.  
The Charity was created in 2016 in response to the founders and trustees experience of meeting women in rural areas of  Cameroon and other parts of the country with little or no access to sustainable education. This brought us to the conclusion that, with the right support, women can play a more crucial role in the development of their economies and improve their financial positions via education...

Objectives  
We intend to craft a full participation agenda, which can be weaved into our country’s policies and practices. We intend to push tradition-bound bureaus and agencies to think differently about the role of women in our societies as agents of growth.

Our Mission
To champion the rights of females and reduce the impact of inequalities so every girl child can benefit from education, so in the future, these females can add value not only to their families but also to the society.

Our Vision
DAF’s vision is of a Cameroon where young females have access to education. To put an end to marginalization. We strive to increase the number of females in education.

Specialties
Internships, Travel, Volunteering,  Coaching, Care Work, Teaching, workshops and Art and Craft


our slogan - "Strong women, strong nation"'}, {'date': {'start': {'month': 11, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}, 'end': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': None}}, 'role': 'Volunteer Administrative Assistant', 'company': {'id': None, 'name': 'TEDxRotterdam', 'logo': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4E0BAQG37BURs13fyw/company-logo_400_400/0/1548401296983?e=1700697600&v=beta&t=YWI8BabhEUQRBK-qobg6Ox60NdZoSHfNK7JWFQuppcA', 'url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/tedxrotterdam/'}, 'cause': 'SCIENCE_AND_TECHNOLOGY', 'description': 'I was part of a determined group of people, with the same vision to reach a common goal.
